				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'd be OK with an FME-7 clone. CPU cycle counters have the disadvantage that you need to translate scanlines into CPU cycles if the Y coordinate of the raster effects are dynamic, and that values are different for PAL and NTSC, but both issues can be solved with look-up tables (about 960 bytes).
<br />
<br />The advantage is that you can use them for purposes other than counting scanlines, since they still work when the PPU is off, and there's nothing the PPU can do that will screw up the counting.</div>

